Use Case 1: Generate Token
Actor: Bank Customer
Precondition:Customer is present in the bank branch
Main Flow:
1.	Customer requests a new token.
2.	System generates a unique token number.
3.	Token is added to the active queue.
4.	Token number is displayed to the customer.
Alternative Flow:
•	If the system is unavailable, token generation fails.
Postcondition:
Customer receives a valid token.

Use Case 2: Call Next Token
Actor:Bank Teller
Precondition:Teller is authenticated and queue is not empty
Main Flow:
1.	Teller selects “Call Next Token.”
2.	System identifies the next token in the queue.
3.	Token is assigned to a service counter.
4.	Token status is updated to “In Service.”
Alternative Flow:
•	If the queue is empty, the system displays a message.
Postcondition:
Next customer is called for service.

Use Case 3: Monitor Queue Performance
Actor:Bank Manager/Administrator
Precondition:Admin is authenticated
Main Flow:
1.	Admin accesses the dashboard.
2.	System displays real-time queue statistics.
3.	Admin reviews performance metrics.
Alternative Flow:
•	If no data is available, system displays default values.
Postcondition:
